<author><name><![CDATA[Hamtaro126]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-03-31T10:47:00-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-03-31T10:47:00-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5003&amp;p=44984#p44984</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5003&amp;p=44984#p44984"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: modding PAL cart to NTSC]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5003&amp;p=44984#p44984"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">bluej774 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I thought I saw somewhere a long time ago that you can take a PAL nes cart and mod it somehow so that it runs at NTSC speed on an NTSC NES.  Is this possible or was it some kind of wonderful dream?<br /></div><br /><br />First, Depending on if there is a NTSC equivlent of the game, You need to extract all of the the NTSC music engine and replace the PAL music engine with the NTSC one. I did that while hacking Ufouria to NTSC<br /><br />Secondly, Disable the CIC Lockout chip by removing it. There is a document on NESWORLD: <a href="http://www.nesworld.com/universalnes.php" class="postlink">http://www.nesworld.com/universalnes.php</a><br /><br />And then after the ROM is done, remove the INES header and split PRG and CHR (Use a tile editor to determine where CHR is, if no CHR, it has CHR-RAM), make your EPROMs or whatever you perfer, desolder the original CHR and PRG rom and resolder the new roms to their places<br /><br />EDIT: CHR Replacement is optional.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=287">Hamtaro126</a> — Tue Mar 31, 2009 10:47 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
